My storyMy name is Anca Fota, I am a dietitian, I love working with people and I also love to cook, to eat and to share with others the best recipes I make in my kitchen.I live in Romania, a beautiful country in Eastern Europe, with wonderful people and a delicious traditional cuisine, with influences throughout history from many other countries.I started my dietitian career almost 3 years ago, at age of 29 years old, when I finally realized that I am free to follow my passion, to do what I like and live a happy life. I graduated a nutrition course and I started helping people to feel good in their body and to eat what they like, but with some small changes so they can lose weight and after that to maintain.I love working with people, encouraging them that they deserve a happy life, that they are great people, they should love themselves just the way they are and, if they want to change something in their weight, I am there to guide them, to listen to them and to make things possible.However, I believe that I have a small part in there, they are the main actor, they must have the desire to change, and I am there only to support and to guide them.In practice I could observe that people would like to eat healthier, but they believe that healthy food is not so tasty. This is how I got to work on finding a way of preparing different dishes in a healthier way, but also with a great taste. Now my work is a real success, people lose weight and maintain very easy because they have changed some small habits, they eat what they like and they are happier.In my book, I want to share with you, some of the most refined and delicious recipes of pancakes from all over the world, but also adapted, from my dietitian perspective, to have as few calories as possible, but the same great taste as the original recipe.I have prepared 52 recipes, one new recipe for every weekend of the year, so Saturday or Sunday, you can indulge your family or your life partner with a great recipe of pancakes cooked with love.I will share with you, with all my love, one of the most exquisite recipe, Nalesniki, thin pancakes filled with fine cheese and garnished with fresh raspberries sauce and fresh fruits. The original recipe is from Eastern Europe countries and Russia, with small differences from country to country.My adapted recipe looks like you could see in my presentation video, is very tasty and very easy to prepare. I dare you to try it as soon as you can!All the ingredients are enough for 6 portions.Ingredients for the batter:
3 large eggs (at room temperature);
20g (2 tablespoons) of organic stevia sweetener (instead of sugar);
Pinch of salt;
60g of melted butter (but not too hot);
240ml of milk (at room temperature);
20g (2 tablespoons) of almond flour;
100g of rice flour.
You can put all the ingredients in a blender and mix it all together, or, you can use a whisk and mix the ingredients in the exact order from the list. You leave the batter to rest for 30 minute, and after that you can start and cook the pancakes in a non-stick pan.In the meantime, you can prepare the filling and the raspberries sauce.Ingredients for the filling:
Mascarpone cheese 250g;
Ricotta cheese 250g;
20g (2 tablespoons) of organic stevia sweetener (instead of sugar);
Pinch of salt;
Vanilla extract;
Lemon zest (from 1 fresh lemon);
1 large egg.
You can put all the ingredients in a large bowl and mix it with a mixer, or you can mix it with a tablespoon for about 5 minutes. You keep the filling in the fridge until you finish cooking the pancakes.Ingredients for the raspberries sauce:
300g of fresh raspberries (or you can use frozen raspberries);
50g (5 tablespoons) of organic stevia sweetener (instead of sugar);
2 tablespoons of lemon juice;
100ml of water.
You cook the raspberries in a small pot, not too long, just until the sweetener is dissolving and the raspberries break. After this, you have to use a strainer and remove the raspberries seeds, so you can have a fine sauce. You keep the sauce in the fridge until the pancakes are ready to serve.After you cook all the batter, you should get 12 thin pancakes, you fill every pancake with the mixed cheese, you put them in a baking vessel and cook in the oven for 15 minutes.When you are ready to serve, you put 2 filled pancakes in a deep plate, 3-4 tablespoons of raspberries sauce and some fresh fruits. I used fresh cranberries and raspberries.Nutritional values for one portion:Protein - 13g;Fat – 34g;Carbohydrates – 23g;Fiber – 4.6g;Calories – 450kcal.This dish is good to be eaten at breakfast, as a brunch or a dessert.Enjoy!If you like this recipe and if you would love to be a supporter, I invite you to select your favorite perk and to join with me in this wonderful journey.With all my love,Ancacontact@ancafota.ro
